<TITLE> 2nd Padma Bridge to be sited at Paturia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com)  Construction of the second Padma Bridge at Goalanda-Paturia point will start soon, with full private sector funding, the finance minister said on Thursday. Abul Maal Abdul Muhith told reporters after a meeting of the cabinet committee on economic affairs: "The committee has approved in principle a proposal to construct the bridge with private financing." "The government will start work on construction of the bridge as soon as possible," he said. To a question on its size, cost and construction time, the minister said: "I cannot say anything about that unless a feasiblility study is done. But it's for sure that we will construct the bridge." The proposal made by the communications ministry said construction of the bridge, which include a 6.1 kilometer rail road, would require $ 1.9 billion (taka 131.21 billion). "Depending on development partners for finance of the bridge will need long time. So initiatives can be taken to construct the bridge under build-operate-transfer (BOT) or public-private partnership (PPP) arrangement during the present government considering it the socio-economic importance," it said
